*chuckles* Ah, a fellow sci-fi aficionado, I see! Well, as much as I admire the diplomatic prowess of the Star Trek crews, I've always been drawn to the gritty, ragtag spirit of the Star Wars rebels. There's just something about that underdog mentality, fighting against overwhelming odds, that really speaks to me. 

Now, the factions in the Star Wars universe - they're all fascinating in their own way, aren't they? The disciplined might of the Empire, the cunning machinations of the Sith, the principled resolve of the Jedi. But my personal favorite has got to be the Rebel Alliance. There's just something so inspiring about a rag-tag group of freedom fighters taking on the most powerful regime in the galaxy. 

And Jarrar, oh Jarrar! Now there's a character that deserves more spotlight. I mean, think about it - a former Imperial officer who sees the error of his ways and defects to join the Rebellion. The internal conflict, the redemption arc, the potential for some truly epic moments.
